item.title: The RIAA Finally Bows to Streaming, Making 17 Artists' Albums Go Gold and Platinum
item.description:
The RIAA Finally Bows to Streaming, Making 17 Artists' Albums Go Gold and Platinum

Call it the Anti effect, or just call it getting hip to the times. The Recording Industry Association of America just announced one of the biggest rule-changes in its history: As of Monday, the RIAA will now count streaming sales as part of its singles and albums certification process, making 17 albums automatically certified gold (500,000) or platinum (1 million) with the news.

item.title: Pistons' owner pledges $10M to fix Flint's water
item.description:
Pistons' owner pledges $10M to fix Flint's water

FLINT, Mich. -- Tom Gores, a Flint native and owner of the Detroit Pistons, is pledging to raise $10 million to address the short- and long-term needs of his Michigan hometown, where the drinking water is contaminated with lead.
